39
40AXIsolatedObject::AXIsolatedObject(AXCoreObject& object, AXIsolatedTree* tree, AXID parentID)
41 : m_cachedTree(tree)
42 , m_parentID(parentID)
43 , m_id(object.objectID())
44{
45 ASSERT(isMainThread());
46 if (m_id != InvalidAXID)
47 initializeAttributeData(object, parentID == InvalidAXID);
48 else {
49 // Should never happen under normal circumstances.
50 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
51 }
52}
53
54Ref<AXIsolatedObject> AXIsolatedObject::create(AXCoreObject& object, AXIsolatedTree* tree, AXID parentID)
55{
56 return adoptRef(*new AXIsolatedObject(object, tree, parentID));
57}
58
59AXIsolatedObject::~AXIsolatedObject()
60{
61 ASSERT(!wrapper());
62}
63
64void AXIsolatedObject::init()
65{
66 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
67}

416
417AXCoreObject* AXIsolatedObject::associatedAXObject() const
418{
419 ASSERT(isMainThread());
420
421 if (m_id == InvalidAXID)
422 return nullptr;
423
424 if (auto* axObjectCache = this->axObjectCache()) {
425 if (auto* axObject = axObjectCache->objectFromAXID(m_id)) {
426 axObject->updateBackingStore();
427 return axObject;
428 }
429 }
430
431 return nullptr;
432}
433
434void AXIsolatedObject::setMathscripts(AXPropertyName propertyName, AXCoreObject& object)
435{
436 AccessibilityMathMultiscriptPairs pairs;
437 if (propertyName == AXPropertyName::MathPrescripts)
438 object.mathPrescripts(pairs);
439 else if (propertyName == AXPropertyName::MathPostscripts)
440 object.mathPostscripts(pairs);
441
442 size_t mathSize = pairs.size();
443 if (!mathSize)
444 return;
445
446 Vector<std::pair<AXID, AXID>> idPairs;
447 idPairs.reserveCapacity(mathSize);
448 for (auto mathPair : pairs) {
449 std::pair<AXID, AXID> idPair;
450 if (mathPair.first)
451 idPair.first = mathPair.first->objectID();
452 if (mathPair.second)
453 idPair.second = mathPair.second->objectID();
454 idPairs.uncheckedAppend(idPair);
455 }
456 setProperty(propertyName, idPairs);
457}
458
459void AXIsolatedObject::setObjectProperty(AXPropertyName propertyName, AXCoreObject* object)
460{
461 if (object)
462 setProperty(propertyName, object->objectID());
463 else
464 setProperty(propertyName, nullptr, true);
465}
466
467void AXIsolatedObject::setObjectVectorProperty(AXPropertyName propertyName, const AccessibilityChildrenVector& children)
468{
469 if (!children.size())
470 return;
471
472 Vector<AXID> childIDs;
473 childIDs.reserveCapacity(children.size());
474
475 for (auto child : children)
476 childIDs.uncheckedAppend(child->objectID());
477
478 setProperty(propertyName, childIDs);
479}
480
481void AXIsolatedObject::setProperty(AXPropertyName propertyName, AXPropertyValueVariant&& value, bool shouldRemove)
482{
483 if (shouldRemove)
484 m_propertyMap.remove(propertyName);
485 else
486 m_propertyMap.set(propertyName, value);
487}
488
489void AXIsolatedObject::setParent(AXID parent)
490{
491 ASSERT(isMainThread());
492 m_parentID = parent;
493}
494
495void AXIsolatedObject::detachRemoteParts(AccessibilityDetachmentType)
496{
497 for (const auto& childID : m_childrenIDs) {
498 if (auto child = tree()->nodeForID(childID))
499 child->detachFromParent();
500 }
501 m_childrenIDs.clear();
502}
503
504bool AXIsolatedObject::isDetached() const
505{
506 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
507 return false;
508}
509
510void AXIsolatedObject::detachFromParent()
511{
512 m_parentID = InvalidAXID;
513}
514
515const AXCoreObject::AccessibilityChildrenVector& AXIsolatedObject::children(bool)
516{
517 ASSERT(_AXSIsolatedTreeModeFunctionIsAvailable() && ((_AXSIsolatedTreeMode_Soft() == AXSIsolatedTreeModeSecondaryThread && !isMainThread())
518 || (_AXSIsolatedTreeMode_Soft() == AXSIsolatedTreeModeMainThread && isMainThread())));
519 updateBackingStore();
520 m_children.clear();
521 m_children.reserveInitialCapacity(m_childrenIDs.size());
522 for (const auto& childID : m_childrenIDs) {
523 if (auto child = tree()->nodeForID(childID))
524 m_children.uncheckedAppend(child);
525 }
526 return m_children;
527}
528
529void AXIsolatedObject::updateChildrenIfNecessary()
530{
531 // FIXME: this is a no-op for isolated objects and should be removed from
532 // the public interface. It is used in the mac implementation of
533 // [WebAccessibilityObjectWrapper accessibilityHitTest].
534}
535
536void AXIsolatedObject::setSelectedChildren(const AccessibilityChildrenVector& selectedChildren)
537{
538 ASSERT(selectedChildren.isEmpty() || (selectedChildren[0] && selectedChildren[0]->isAXIsolatedObjectInstance()));
539
540 performFunctionOnMainThread([&] (AXCoreObject* object) {
541 if (selectedChildren.isEmpty()) {
542 // No selection, no need to convert objects from isolated to live.
543 object->setSelectedChildren(selectedChildren);
544 return;
545 }
546
547 auto* axObjectCache = this->axObjectCache();
548 if (!axObjectCache)
549 return;
550
551 auto axIDs = tree()->idsForObjects(selectedChildren);
552 auto axSelectedChildren = axObjectCache->objectsForIDs(axIDs);
553 object->setSelectedChildren(axSelectedChildren);
554 });
555}
556
557bool AXIsolatedObject::isDetachedFromParent()
558{
559 if (parent() != InvalidAXID)
560 return false;
561
562 // Check whether this is the root node, in which case we should return false.
563 if (auto root = tree()->rootNode())
564 return root->objectID() != m_id;
565 return false;
566}
567
568AXCoreObject* AXIsolatedObject::cellForColumnAndRow(unsigned columnIndex, unsigned rowIndex)
569{
570 AXID cellID = Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<AXID>([&columnIndex, &rowIndex, this] () -> AXID {
571 if (auto* object = associatedAXObject()) {
572 if (auto cell = object->cellForColumnAndRow(columnIndex, rowIndex))
573 return cell->objectID();
574 }
575 return InvalidAXID;
576 });
577
578 return tree()->nodeForID(cellID).get();
579}

620void AXIsolatedObject::insertMathPairs(Vector<std::pair<AXID, AXID>>& isolatedPairs, AccessibilityMathMultiscriptPairs& pairs)
621{
622 for (const auto& pair : isolatedPairs) {
623 AccessibilityMathMultiscriptPair prescriptPair;
624 if (auto coreObject = tree()->nodeForID(pair.first).get())
625 prescriptPair.first = coreObject;
626 if (auto coreObject = tree()->nodeForID(pair.second).get())
627 prescriptPair.second = coreObject;
628 pairs.append(prescriptPair);
629 }
630}
631
632void AXIsolatedObject::mathPrescripts(AccessibilityMathMultiscriptPairs& pairs)
633{
634 auto isolatedPairs = vectorAttributeValue<std::pair<AXID, AXID>>(AXPropertyName::MathPrescripts);
635 insertMathPairs(isolatedPairs, pairs);
636}

641 insertMathPairs(isolatedPairs, pairs);
642}

786AXCoreObject* AXIsolatedObject::accessibilityHitTest(const IntPoint& point) const
787{
788 AXID axID = Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<AXID>([&point, this] () -> AXID {
789 if (auto* object = associatedAXObject()) {
790 object->updateChildrenIfNecessary();
791 if (auto* axObject = object->accessibilityHitTest(point))
792 return axObject->objectID();
793 }
794
795 return InvalidAXID;
796 });
797
798 return tree()->nodeForID(axID).get();
799}

1698bool AXIsolatedObject::hasSameFont(const AXCoreObject& otherObject) const
1699{
1700 if (!is<AXIsolatedObject>(otherObject))
1701 return false;
1702
1703 return Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<bool>([&otherObject, this] () -> bool {
1704 if (auto* axObject = associatedAXObject()) {
1705 if (auto* axOtherObject = downcast<AXIsolatedObject>(otherObject).associatedAXObject())
1706 return axObject->hasSameFont(*axOtherObject);
1707 }
1708 return false;
1709 });
1710}

2392String AXIsolatedObject::innerHTML() const
2393{
2394 if (m_propertyMap.contains(AXPropertyName::InnerHTML))
2395 return stringAttributeValue(AXPropertyName::InnerHTML);
2396
2397 return Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<String>([this] () -> String {
2398 auto* axObject = associatedAXObject();
2399 String value = axObject ? axObject->innerHTML().isolatedCopy() : String();
2400
2401 // Cache value so that there is no need to access the main thread in subsequent calls.
2402 const_cast<AXIsolatedObject*>(this)->setProperty(AXPropertyName::InnerHTML, value);
2403
2404 return value;
2405 });
2406}
2407
2408String AXIsolatedObject::outerHTML() const
2409{

2411 return stringAttributeValue(AXPropertyName::OuterHTML);
2412
2413 return Accessibility::retrieveValueFromMainThread<String>([this] () -> String {
2414 auto* axObject = associatedAXObject();
2415 String value = axObject ? axObject->outerHTML().isolatedCopy() : String();
2416
2417 // Cache value so that there is no need to access the main thread in subsequent calls.
2418 const_cast<AXIsolatedObject*>(this)->setProperty(AXPropertyName::OuterHTML, value);
2419
2420 return value;
2421 });
